-- Germany to Meet Maastricht Deficit Guidelines by 2012, Handelsblatt Says
-- Aaron Kirchfeld
-- 2010-07-15T05:06:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/germany-to-meet-maastricht-deficit-guidelines-by-2012-handelsblatt-says.html

          
          
             German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  plans to cut the deficit to 3 percent of gross
domestic product by 2012 to meet the Maastricht Treaty criteria
earlier than expected,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing
unidentified participants at a meeting of federal, state and
local authorities.  
 The deficit is forecast to decline to 4.5 percent this
year, 4 percent in 2011, 3 percent in 2012, 2 percent in 2013,
and 1 percent in 2014, the newspaper reported. It said
Bundesbank President  Axel Weber  pushed for aggressive budget
cuts.  
